3.6 Login by Checker:  
a. Approve/Reject BC & OR plan  
Step 1: Click on “+Plan” and then “Pending as Branch Checker”. Checker can view all the details and provide approval if the Plan is in 
order. In case of any discrepancies the plan may be rejected by the Checker. All 7 parts need to be verified before approving or rejecting.   
23  
Step 2: After verifying, the checker needs to approve or reject the plan. Rejecting the plan by Checker will put the plan on the tray of 
Maker. The checker can put comments stating the reason for rejecting the proposal. Approving the plan leads to submission of the plan 
to Alternate Branch/Office Checker. Once rejected, it will be shown as draft in the Maker tab.  
24  
25  
  
3.7 Login by Checker:  
  
a. Approve/Reject BC & OR Testing report  
  
Step 1: Click on “Testing” and then “Pending with Checker”. Checker can view all the details and provide approval if the testing is in order. 
Save and Next to visit next page.  
 
  
  
Step 2: After verifying all parts, the Checker needs to approve or reject the testing report. Rejecting the testing report by Checker will put 
it on the tray of Maker. The Checker can put comments stating the reason for rejecting.  Approving the testing report leads to submission 
of the same to the Controller.  Once rejected, it will be shown as draft in the Maker tab.  
26  
3.8 Login by Checker  
a. Approve/Reject BC & OR Invocation report  
Step 1: Click on “Invocation” and then “Pending with Checker”. Checker can view all the details and provide approval if the Invocation 
Report and Resilience Matrix are in order. In case of any discrepancies, the same may be rejected by the Checker. Rejecting the report 
by Checker will put it in the tray of Maker. The Checker can put comments stating the reason for rejecting the report.  Approving the 
report leads to submission of Invocation Report to the Controller. Once rejected, it will be shown as draft in the Maker tab.  
27  
28  
  
 
  
 
  
  
 
 
 
 
 
 
29  
  
3.9 Login by Alternate Branch/Office Checker:  
  
a. Approve/Reject BC & OR plan  
  
Step 1: Click on “+Plan” and then “Pending as Alternate Branch Checker” and provide approval if the Plan is in order. In case of any 
discrepancies, the plan may be rejected by the Checker. All 7 parts need to be verified.   
 
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
Step 2: After verifying all 7 parts, the Checker needs to approve or reject the plan. Rejecting the plan by Alternate Branch/Office Checker 
will put the plan in the tray of Maker. The Checker can put comments stating the reason for rejecting the plan.  Accepting the plan leads 
to submission of plan to the Controller. Once rejected, it will be shown as draft in the Maker tab.  
30  
31  
  
3.10 Login by Controller  
  
a. Approve/Reject BC & OR plan  
Controller can view all the details and provide approval if the Plan is in order. In case of any discrepancies the plan may also be rejected 
by the Controller. All 7 parts need to be verified before approving/rejecting the plan. Once rejected, it will be shown as draft in the Maker 
tab. 
 
 
  
 
  
  
b. Approve/Reject BC & OR Testing report  
Controller can view all the details and provide approval if the testing report is in order.  
In case of any discrepancies, the report may be rejected by the controller. Once rejected, it will be shown as draft in the Maker tab. 
32  
c. Approve/Reject BC & OR Invocation report  
Controller can view all the details and provide approval if the invocation report is in order. In case of any discrepancies, the invocation 
report may be rejected by the controller. Once rejected, it will be shown as draft in the Maker tab.  
33  
34  
  
